-- Mauritius Leasing Heads for Its 15-Month High on Trading Halt
-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 2012-03-20T09:43:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-20/mauritius-leasing-heads-for-its-15-month-high-on-trading-halt.html
Mauritius Leasing Co. Ltd. (MLC) , a
provider of leasing facilities for movable assets and equipment,
surged to its highest in 15 months before trading is suspended
as the company completes its merger.  The stock jumped 19 percent to 8.9 rupees by the close in
Port Louis, the capital, the strongest daily rise since December
2010, according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  Trading in shares will be suspended from March 28 until the
completion of its merger with Bramer Banking Corp Ltd. and
Bramer Holding Co. Ltd. The shareholders are scheduled to
approve the merger on April 16, the company said in a  statement 
on the Stock Exchange of Mauritius today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
